I wrote many different captions for this and deleted them all cause I don’t really know how to wrap up my thoughts about this. I think we all have a warped sense of what bodies should look like, myself included, inundated daily across the internet with images of body “perfection” to the point of feeling repulsed by our own bodies. Muscles are adored and validated and lusted after, tummies and folds are not. No one’s posting the images that aren’t “perfect”. Look after yourselves, drink more water. And you look great in these Cameron❤️✨ @cpostnik

I photographed @isaiahrburgess across two days on film, digital, and iPhone and we came away with a set of really beautiful images that aren’t only fascinating to look at cause the body is bodying (whatever) but the way he brought so much more than that to every frame, like if I could paint I’d paint some of these. 50 images now up on my website, link in stories ✨

@samsmith at the Forum LA. 

I began seriously taking photos in 2005 and for the first few years I was a music concert/festival photographer and I wanna thank Sam for getting me back in that pit. I’ve never shot a concert on medium format film either (hasselblad 503cx) so that was interesting and go me for the shots actually working.

@danielgarofali 2009. After 4 years of taking photos in nightclubs, parties and music festivals I wanted to start making portraits and teaching myself how to use strobes etc. This was my very first planned shoot with a model, backdrop, lighting…and filling my living room with flour.
